WEBVTT

00:01.523 --> 00:03.424
-Previously on "Get Shorty"...

00:03.524 --> 00:04.986
-You're standing by the deal
that we made, right?

00:05.086 --> 00:08.549
-No. Someone very high up
wants to make an example of you.

00:08.649 --> 00:11.672
-Can you honor
Louis' side of the deal?

00:11.772 --> 00:14.194
-From the description of
your conversation with Amara,

00:14.294 --> 00:16.436
it's possible she has no idea
you're working with us.

00:16.536 --> 00:18.158
-Yes, and it's also possible
she does.

00:18.258 --> 00:19.479
-Serve a long enough sentence,

00:19.579 --> 00:21.361
no one will know
you were an informant.

00:21.461 --> 00:23.603
-You're actually pitching this?
That I choose to go to prison?

00:23.703 --> 00:25.885
-Bend over. Cough.

00:25.985 --> 00:27.246
[ Men coughing ]

00:27.346 --> 00:28.567
♪♪♪

00:28.667 --> 00:31.290
-Uh, yeah.
I'm here to go to prison.

00:31.390 --> 00:32.771
[ Men shouting, cheering ]

00:32.871 --> 00:36.054
-Who runs Capotillo in here?
-Swayze.

00:36.154 --> 00:38.777
I heard one of the Latvians was
talking shit about Swayze.

00:38.877 --> 00:40.458
He sent them a pickle jar,

00:40.558 --> 00:44.462
and on the inside,
their boy's dick and balls.

00:44.562 --> 00:47.465
-Are you saying that
I can come back?

00:47.565 --> 00:51.709
-If this shit with Amara
is really in the past --

00:51.809 --> 00:53.310
-It is.

00:53.410 --> 00:56.032
-I'm staying on "Wylderness"
as a producer.

00:56.133 --> 00:58.635
-You don't think that could be
awkward -- us working together?

00:58.735 --> 01:00.517
-Not if you stay out of my way.

01:00.617 --> 01:02.278
-They cast Amanda Rhodes.

01:02.378 --> 01:06.322
-No. No, she's --
Oh. She's all wrong.

01:06.422 --> 01:10.005
-Why do you care?
-'Cause my fucking name's on it.

01:10.105 --> 01:12.648
Hey, maybe I could get
some notes to April.

01:12.748 --> 01:14.129
-[ Grunts ]

01:14.229 --> 01:15.090
[ All shouting ]

01:15.190 --> 01:16.491
-Hey!

01:16.591 --> 01:20.695
[ Shouting continues ]

01:20.795 --> 01:24.018
[ Alarm blaring ]

01:24.118 --> 01:26.120
-Yago!

01:29.363 --> 01:31.545
[ Electricity humming ]

01:31.645 --> 01:34.748
[ Man coughs ]

01:34.848 --> 01:37.150
[ Doors slam shut ]

01:37.250 --> 01:39.612
[ Keys jingling ]

01:50.342 --> 01:52.704
[ Keys jingling ]

01:58.790 --> 02:01.112
[ Door buzzes ]

02:03.154 --> 02:05.636
[ Whistling in distance ]

02:21.010 --> 02:23.533
[ Man whistles ]

02:29.018 --> 02:30.879
-What is that?

02:30.979 --> 02:33.482
-Passing something.

02:33.582 --> 02:35.564
-Passing what?

02:35.664 --> 02:37.746
-Who the fuck cares?

02:50.197 --> 03:00.206
♪♪♪

03:00.607 --> 03:10.756
♪♪♪

03:10.856 --> 03:14.660
♪♪♪

03:17.862 --> 03:20.505
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:27.711 --> 03:30.134
-You've got it down.

03:30.234 --> 03:32.376
-Guards want 10 a minute.

03:32.476 --> 03:34.338
-10 a minute?

03:34.438 --> 03:36.820
600 an hour.

03:36.920 --> 03:40.663
Three hours a day,
that's 1,800 souvenirs.

03:40.763 --> 03:42.625
Multiply that by five years,
that's...

03:42.725 --> 03:44.787
I mean, who even buys this shit?

03:44.887 --> 03:47.289
[ Indistinct talking ]

03:49.772 --> 03:53.335
Fabian, would you mind
movin' for a minute?

03:58.099 --> 04:00.622
Hey.
Can Yago have your seat?

04:03.104 --> 04:05.846
For a book of stamps.

04:05.946 --> 04:08.229
And some goldfish?

04:10.391 --> 04:12.673
Thank you. [ Whistles ]

04:20.360 --> 04:23.703
They patch you up?

04:23.803 --> 04:26.465
-Doctor said I was lucky
it missed my spleen.

04:26.565 --> 04:28.647
Whatever the fuck that is.

04:32.211 --> 04:35.434
-Cellmate thinks Capotillo
didn't put the hit on me.

04:35.534 --> 04:37.716
It was Amara.

04:37.816 --> 04:40.538
-You heard that?
-I Think everyone heard.

04:46.784 --> 04:49.947
-My Tia paid someone
to fuckin' kill me.

04:53.950 --> 04:56.293
Hurts, you know?

04:56.393 --> 04:58.815
More than the stitches.

04:58.915 --> 05:00.296
-I'm starting to think
she's not the soft,

05:00.396 --> 05:02.218
sentimental old lady
we thought she was.

05:02.318 --> 05:05.701
[ Door buzzes ]

05:05.801 --> 05:07.963
-That fucking guy?

05:09.044 --> 05:12.628
[ Scoffs ]
Already out of solitary.

05:12.728 --> 05:15.831
-I hear his nickname is "Happy."

05:15.931 --> 05:18.753
Who says inmates
don't have a sense of irony.

05:18.853 --> 05:21.235
-Guards said we got
in an "argument."

05:21.336 --> 05:22.557
What fucking argument?

05:22.657 --> 05:24.719
He stabs me,

05:24.819 --> 05:28.642
and then, they let him out
so he can do it again.

05:28.742 --> 05:30.724
-On the bright side,
Capotillo now know

05:30.824 --> 05:33.106
that we're not
running with Amara.

05:36.830 --> 05:38.832
-Get anywhere with Swayze?

05:40.073 --> 05:42.075
-Workin' on it.

05:44.837 --> 05:45.778
-You know what?

05:45.878 --> 05:47.500
If it wasn't for you,

05:47.600 --> 05:51.944
I'd have a lot more
than 12 stitches right now.

05:52.044 --> 05:54.106
I'm saying I owe you.

05:54.206 --> 05:56.208
-Yes, you do.

06:02.854 --> 06:05.376
[ Water running ]

06:06.857 --> 06:08.879
[ Indistinct conversation ]

06:08.979 --> 06:11.061
[ Door slams shut ]

06:27.276 --> 06:29.718
-You stay.

06:35.924 --> 06:38.586
-My girl, Natasha.

06:38.686 --> 06:41.589
You got her a job
doing makeup on a movie?

06:41.689 --> 06:43.591
-I did, yeah.

06:43.691 --> 06:45.753
-Wow.

06:45.853 --> 06:48.596
I'm so grateful.

06:48.696 --> 06:49.957
What can I do for you?

06:50.057 --> 06:52.359
-Well, right now,
I could use a towel.

06:52.459 --> 06:57.003
It's a bit chilly in here,
as you may have noticed.

06:57.103 --> 06:59.766
The job was just
a peace offering.

06:59.866 --> 07:02.568
I know that Amara and Capotillo
haven't been getting

07:02.668 --> 07:06.172
along very well,
but I'm not with Amara now.

07:06.272 --> 07:08.934
In fact, she just ordered
a hit on my buddy, Yago.

07:09.034 --> 07:11.016
-You want protection?

07:11.116 --> 07:13.659
-That would be great.
-That it?

07:13.759 --> 07:15.380
-I could also use some help
getting materials

07:15.480 --> 07:17.222
in and out of this place.

07:17.322 --> 07:20.665
Nothing major.
Just written notes.

07:20.765 --> 07:22.887
-Notes?

07:26.450 --> 07:28.032
Okay.

07:28.132 --> 07:30.434
-Really?

07:30.534 --> 07:31.835
-Want them delivered
to your cell,

07:31.935 --> 07:34.798
like in wrapping paper?

07:34.898 --> 07:39.042
[ Laughter ]

07:39.142 --> 07:42.885
You think I need help
getting my girls jobs?

07:42.985 --> 07:44.767
-He got five girls.

07:44.867 --> 07:48.691
-Natasha, not even my favorite.

07:48.791 --> 07:51.373
-I thought she seemed nice.

07:51.473 --> 07:54.856
-You try this shit again...

07:54.956 --> 07:58.259
your buddy's gonna get a pickle
jar with your pinche verga.

07:58.359 --> 08:01.102
-Need a translation?

08:01.202 --> 08:03.204
-I think I got it.

08:07.087 --> 08:09.870
I hear your brother
has a trucking company.

08:09.970 --> 08:13.033
Maybe I could get him
a contract.

08:13.133 --> 08:14.875
-This guy.
-Shut him the fuck up.

08:14.975 --> 08:17.197
-It would be worth
20 grand a week.

08:17.297 --> 08:19.539
-Hold up, hold up.

08:21.981 --> 08:23.723
A week?

08:23.823 --> 08:25.284
-Maybe I could grab that towel

08:25.384 --> 08:27.586
and we could
discuss this further?

08:31.990 --> 08:39.217
♪♪♪

08:39.317 --> 08:41.939
[ Horn honks ]

08:42.039 --> 08:48.706
♪♪♪

08:48.806 --> 08:50.227
-April! Over here.
[ Device beeping ]

08:50.327 --> 08:53.470
-Oh.
This is so confusing.

08:53.570 --> 08:55.031
The apartment numbers
go up that way,

08:55.131 --> 08:56.152
and then they just go back down.

08:56.253 --> 08:58.034
-Yeah, I don't understand,
either.

08:58.134 --> 08:59.556
Everybody gets lost.

08:59.656 --> 09:03.559
-What's that beeping?
-Oh, it's my ankle monitor.

09:03.659 --> 09:08.564
Yeah, I got 60 seconds to get
back in range, so come on in.

09:08.664 --> 09:10.886
-Hi.
-Oh, my God.

09:10.986 --> 09:12.968
-Right?
-How soon?

09:13.068 --> 09:14.569
-Super soon, like any week.

09:14.669 --> 09:16.891
-Oh, my God.

09:16.992 --> 09:19.694
-We're having a home birth.
-Are you?

09:19.794 --> 09:21.736
-Yeah, tried for special
dispensation

09:21.836 --> 09:23.738
for the ankle monitor,

09:23.838 --> 09:27.942
but my probation officer
keeps jerking me around.

09:28.042 --> 09:29.343
-Yes.
So many people that I know

09:29.443 --> 09:31.265
have the baby at home
with a midwife.

09:31.365 --> 09:32.866
They say, in some ways,
it's safer.

09:32.966 --> 09:35.989
-Less germs.
-Great. [ Laughs ]

09:36.089 --> 09:37.951
I mean, I would never
do it, but...

09:38.051 --> 09:40.593
-Well, you know...

09:40.693 --> 09:42.955
Oh, and who we got.
-Ah?

09:43.055 --> 09:45.558
-She delivered, uh --
-Emily Blunt.

09:45.658 --> 09:46.959
-Emily Blunt's baby.
-Mm-hmm.

09:47.059 --> 09:48.320
-Wow.
-All right.

09:48.420 --> 09:50.362
You guys talk business.

09:50.462 --> 09:52.904
I'll make us some lunch.
-Thanks, honey.

09:56.268 --> 09:58.470
We should sit.

10:00.832 --> 10:04.975
So, you got my e-mail
about the trucking company?

10:05.076 --> 10:10.340
-Louis, from now on,
everything I do is aboveboard.

10:10.440 --> 10:11.982
-These guys are legit.

10:12.082 --> 10:14.985
Casales Transportation
and Refrigeration.

10:15.085 --> 10:17.907
-Since when have you cared
about transportation?

10:18.007 --> 10:21.631
I let your hire a makeup girl
who has never done a feature.

10:21.731 --> 10:23.713
You still won't tell me
what that's about.

10:23.813 --> 10:25.634
-All of this is
aboveboard, just...

10:25.735 --> 10:27.997
[ Microwave beeps, humming ]

10:28.097 --> 10:29.798
It'll help Miles.

10:29.898 --> 10:32.321
If you want, I'll explain how.
-Please don't.

10:32.421 --> 10:34.322
-That's really it. It's just --
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

10:34.422 --> 10:38.606
Oh, wait. Actually,
Miles had a couple of notes.

10:38.706 --> 10:40.048
-What?
-Yeah, he's really not crazy

10:40.148 --> 10:42.850
about Amanda Rhodes
for the lead.

10:42.950 --> 10:44.652
Says that she's too Disney.

10:44.752 --> 10:48.455
-She's doing very big films.
-And he had some story notes.

10:48.555 --> 10:52.019
I tried to write 'em down.
I tried, but it just didn't --

10:52.119 --> 10:54.621
It'd be better
if he just told you himself.

10:54.721 --> 10:56.663
-No.
If he wanted to be involved,

10:56.763 --> 10:58.464
he should have stayed
out of prison.

10:58.565 --> 11:01.227
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

11:01.327 --> 11:04.830
-Well, maybe you could
go see him and tell him that.

11:04.930 --> 11:08.193
-Louis, I am not --
-Miles has a vision

11:08.294 --> 11:09.675
for this movie.

11:09.775 --> 11:11.276
Having something
that he cares about,

11:11.376 --> 11:14.479
something that he is passionate
about while he's inside,

11:14.579 --> 11:18.683
that's gonna keep him going.

11:18.783 --> 11:20.445
-God...

11:20.545 --> 11:25.209
♪♪♪

11:25.309 --> 11:27.291
-Eilert Lovborg was more to you

11:27.391 --> 11:30.374
than perhaps you are
willing to admit.

11:30.474 --> 11:32.456
Am I wrong?

11:32.556 --> 11:36.179
-I don't answer such questions.

11:36.279 --> 11:40.063
Oh, that he had the will
and the strength

11:40.163 --> 11:46.268
to turn away from
the banquet of life so early.

11:46.368 --> 11:49.872
I'm sorry, Mrs. Hedda,
but I fear I must dispel

11:49.972 --> 11:51.873
an amiable illusion...
-Illusion?

11:51.974 --> 11:53.395
-...that could not
have lasted long

11:53.495 --> 11:55.116
in any case.

11:55.217 --> 11:58.840
Eilert Lovborg did not
shoot himself voluntarily.

11:58.940 --> 12:01.022
-Okay, let's stop.

12:03.184 --> 12:07.608
Clive, remember you're
really jealous of Lovborg.

12:07.708 --> 12:11.011
So when you're asking if she has
feelings for him, that hurts.

12:11.111 --> 12:12.012
-Right.
-Yeah.

12:12.112 --> 12:13.213
-Got it.

12:13.313 --> 12:14.614
-And I'm not giving Brack
anything.

12:14.714 --> 12:16.256
Is that coming across
when I'm turning away?

12:16.356 --> 12:17.897
-No, we're getting that.
That's great.

12:17.997 --> 12:19.339
Let's go, um...

12:19.439 --> 12:22.141
Let's go from the line, uh...

12:22.241 --> 12:25.945
-R-R-Rick, can I say,
you are a phenomenal director.

12:26.045 --> 12:27.746
The way you know
what the character wants.

12:27.846 --> 12:29.068
-The subtext.

12:29.168 --> 12:32.270
-Really, you see
the human condition.

12:32.371 --> 12:33.512
It's a gift.

12:33.612 --> 12:36.514
-Wow. Thank you.

12:36.614 --> 12:39.317
It's a very nice compliment.

12:39.417 --> 12:41.419
Thank you.

12:44.261 --> 12:48.786
Okay. So, uh, from Judge Brack,
"Am I wrong?"

12:50.827 --> 12:54.451
-Am I wrong?
-I don't answer such questions.

12:54.551 --> 12:57.293
-I only know that Eilert Lovborg
has had the courage

12:57.393 --> 12:59.135
to live his life
after his own fashion.

12:59.235 --> 13:01.657
[ Door buzzes ]

13:01.757 --> 13:04.200
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:06.081 --> 13:08.143
-Oh, man, it's so good
to see you.

13:08.243 --> 13:10.065
And don't you look well?

13:10.165 --> 13:11.166
I heard that you were back
on the film,

13:11.246 --> 13:13.068
and I thought, "Good on you."

13:13.168 --> 13:14.269
Good for you, April Quinn.

13:14.369 --> 13:16.271
Don't let that spoiled,
arrogant shitbag

13:16.371 --> 13:17.552
push you around.

13:17.652 --> 13:19.354
Time's up.
Am I right?

13:19.454 --> 13:23.197
-Miles, I came in here
to see how you were.

13:23.297 --> 13:26.560
But I have to tell you,
I felt betrayed.

13:26.660 --> 13:28.802
To find out there's
another side of you,

13:28.902 --> 13:31.885
and of our work together
that you never mentioned,

13:31.985 --> 13:35.128
that you made me
an accomplice to felonies

13:35.228 --> 13:37.410
without considering
what it could do to me.

13:37.510 --> 13:40.533
It's a miracle
I still have a career.

13:40.633 --> 13:42.175
-You have every right
to be angry.

13:42.275 --> 13:44.216
-Well...

13:44.316 --> 13:46.819
now I'm seeing these creepy
people you're in here with,

13:46.919 --> 13:49.181
and the...

13:49.281 --> 13:52.504
outfit they make you wear,
and...

13:52.604 --> 13:54.186
it's hard to hold on
to my anger.

13:54.286 --> 13:58.149
-If we can just get back
to "Wylderness," real quick?

13:58.249 --> 13:59.631
Louis mentioned the new ending.

13:59.731 --> 14:01.792
-No, we can't.
-Where she finds her father,

14:01.893 --> 14:05.436
and they fall into each other's
arms, and it's all peachy again?

14:05.536 --> 14:07.358
What the fuck is that?

14:07.458 --> 14:10.561
-We have a great team
of veteran filmmakers.

14:10.661 --> 14:12.362
-Given what happened with
"The Admiral's Mistress,"

14:12.462 --> 14:13.723
that means fuck-all.

14:13.824 --> 14:15.245
-Miles, we're
starting production.

14:15.345 --> 14:17.367
You haven't seen
the latest draft,

14:17.467 --> 14:19.609
and I can't bring you
a new script.

14:19.709 --> 14:22.411
These guards won't let me
bring sugarless gum.

14:22.511 --> 14:24.013
Literally, I had sugarless gum.

14:24.113 --> 14:28.057
-Okay, so I--
[ Door buzzes ]

14:28.157 --> 14:29.378
I'll find another way.

14:29.478 --> 14:31.980
-A legal way?

14:32.080 --> 14:33.221
When you get all whisper-y,

14:33.321 --> 14:36.184
and you're looking
over your shoulder?

14:36.284 --> 14:38.626
-Cath has gone about this
all wrong, April.

14:38.726 --> 14:40.228
I mean, she wanted
the Disney girl,

14:40.328 --> 14:42.430
and now she's messing
with the ending...

14:42.530 --> 14:44.031
I mean, that's not our movie.

14:44.131 --> 14:46.754
This isn't a fuckin' fairy tale.

14:46.854 --> 14:48.355
It's what I'm going through
right now.

14:48.455 --> 14:49.877
It's about people who have
had their lives

14:49.977 --> 14:51.238
pulled from under them,

14:51.338 --> 14:53.160
and they're trying
to fight their way out.

14:53.260 --> 14:54.761
-And they're dealing
with cannibals.

14:54.861 --> 14:56.643
-You don't think
there's cannibals in here?!

14:56.743 --> 14:58.244
April, you once told me

14:58.344 --> 15:00.847
that I was a great producer.
You know what?

15:00.947 --> 15:02.568
I've come to agree with you.

15:02.668 --> 15:05.571
So, please, just let me
keep my hand in.

15:05.671 --> 15:07.913
I can fucking help.

15:08.353 --> 15:14.059
♪♪♪

15:14.159 --> 15:16.781
[ Cellphone beeping ]

15:16.881 --> 15:21.025
[ Phone ringing ]

15:21.125 --> 15:23.307
-Hey.
-You ready?

15:23.407 --> 15:25.309
-Remember where we left off?

15:25.409 --> 15:27.191
-More or less.

15:27.291 --> 15:29.673
♪♪♪

15:29.773 --> 15:33.036
-Okay.
So, Clementine's freaking out

15:33.136 --> 15:36.319
for the file
about her and Joel.

15:36.419 --> 15:41.324
Now she's in the car,
checking an address.

15:41.424 --> 15:43.466
Hold on.

15:45.508 --> 15:47.750
-Shorty, you there?

15:51.713 --> 15:53.655
-Thought Mom was coming in.

15:53.755 --> 15:55.497
She's gone now.

15:55.597 --> 15:57.659
-Would she be angrier
that you're watching a movie

15:57.759 --> 16:00.421
before bed
or that you're talking to me?

16:00.521 --> 16:03.104
-Let's not find out.

16:03.204 --> 16:05.886
Okay.
She's walking into a building.

16:08.609 --> 16:09.950
[ Door slams shut ]

16:10.050 --> 16:11.471
Looking at the people
who live there.

16:11.571 --> 16:13.313
-[ Snoring ]

16:13.413 --> 16:17.437
[ Keys jingle ]

16:17.537 --> 16:21.160
-Dad?

16:21.260 --> 16:22.361
-Hey.

16:22.461 --> 16:25.124
-Everything okay?
-Yeah.

16:25.224 --> 16:26.325
Let's keep going.

16:26.425 --> 16:28.887
-Um... okay.

16:28.987 --> 16:31.330
So, Joel's friend
recognized her.

16:31.430 --> 16:34.452
She used to know him
but doesn't remember.

16:34.552 --> 16:36.054
Okay, now she's
in Joel's apartment.

16:36.154 --> 16:44.462
♪♪♪

16:44.562 --> 16:54.571
♪♪♪

16:56.092 --> 17:00.156
-April?
-Aah! Jesus.

17:00.256 --> 17:02.298
Yeah.
-Got notes from Miles.

17:03.979 --> 17:06.302
-[ Sighs ]

17:09.064 --> 17:11.286
What's your name?
-Oggie.

17:11.386 --> 17:13.528
-Oggie, you scared the shit
out of me.

17:13.628 --> 17:16.731
-Sorry.
-Okay, look.

17:16.831 --> 17:18.413
This is not how
this is going to work.

17:18.513 --> 17:20.535
You do not follow me
on the street.

17:20.635 --> 17:22.817
-Miles said I was suppo--
-I don't care what Miles said.

17:22.917 --> 17:24.899
If you have notes for me,
you bring them to me

17:24.999 --> 17:27.181
at my office or on set.

17:27.281 --> 17:31.345
You call my office
and you set up a time.

17:31.445 --> 17:33.026
-Your office?
-Yes.

17:33.126 --> 17:34.387
Number's there.

17:34.487 --> 17:36.489
You'll need to show a license
at the gate.

17:40.853 --> 17:43.816
The notes are on paper towel?
-Yeah.

17:47.499 --> 17:49.701
-Thank you, Oggie.

17:54.346 --> 17:55.927
[ Sighs ]

17:56.027 --> 17:58.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:09.640 --> 18:12.182
[ Wind blowing, birds cawing ]

18:12.282 --> 18:20.149
♪♪♪

18:20.249 --> 18:24.473
-Still a long way to go.
-We'll get there.

18:24.573 --> 18:26.555
Couple more hours
and we'll stop for the night.

18:26.655 --> 18:29.238
-Can we make a fire?

18:29.338 --> 18:31.079
-Not tonight.
It's not safe.

18:31.179 --> 18:32.601
-Cut!
-That's a cut!

18:32.701 --> 18:36.845
-Natasha, more sweat.
-Yo, they want more sweat.

18:36.945 --> 18:39.227
-On the forehead?

18:44.191 --> 18:46.293
-Cath, I have an idea.

18:46.393 --> 18:47.374
What do you think if --

18:47.474 --> 18:48.575
-Hello.
-Hey.

18:48.675 --> 18:50.097
How's it going?

18:50.197 --> 18:51.418
-Hey.
-Mwah.

18:51.518 --> 18:52.499
-Have you been watching?
-Thank you.

18:52.599 --> 18:53.580
Just this one scene.

18:53.680 --> 18:55.261
He is really good.
-Oh, David?

18:55.361 --> 18:56.583
He's wonderful.
-Wow.

18:56.683 --> 18:58.024
-Wonderful.
-Oh, April, there's someone

18:58.124 --> 18:59.265
asking for you
at basecamp down there.

18:59.365 --> 19:02.228
-Oh.
-All right, good.

19:02.328 --> 19:04.470
You okay?
-Mm-hmm.

19:04.570 --> 19:07.312
[ Indistinct conversation ]

19:07.413 --> 19:17.422
♪♪♪

19:18.222 --> 19:21.085
♪♪♪

19:21.185 --> 19:24.288
[ Pan sizzling ]

19:24.388 --> 19:34.397
♪♪♪

19:35.158 --> 19:45.167
♪♪♪

19:45.608 --> 19:53.355
♪♪♪

19:53.455 --> 20:01.963
♪♪♪

20:02.063 --> 20:04.245
-Beautiful.

20:04.345 --> 20:06.987
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:11.751 --> 20:14.974
[ Door buzzes ]

20:15.075 --> 20:17.637
-Man, why are some
of them pages blue?

20:20.800 --> 20:23.742
-These are rewrites.

20:23.843 --> 20:26.905
See here?
Where they have the stars?

20:27.005 --> 20:29.748
These are lines
that I had 'em put in.

20:29.848 --> 20:31.990
-Hmm.

20:32.090 --> 20:34.672
-Oh, these are good.

20:34.773 --> 20:38.076
-So, uh...

20:38.176 --> 20:40.158
How's the income
from the trucking gig?

20:40.258 --> 20:41.198
It's flowing, right?

20:41.299 --> 20:43.000
-Mm-hmm.
-Great.

20:43.100 --> 20:45.562
So, you know that dude, Happy?

20:45.663 --> 20:49.566
Think you could keep him
away from me?

20:49.666 --> 20:51.368
-I'll talk to Swayze.
-That'd be great, man.

20:51.468 --> 20:54.331
That's all I'm asking.
Thank you.

20:54.431 --> 20:56.993
[ Door buzzes ]

21:01.677 --> 21:03.899
You know, if they catch us
bringing this shit in,

21:03.999 --> 21:05.541
they could add five years
to our bid, right?

21:05.641 --> 21:09.184
-Mm-hmm.

21:09.284 --> 21:12.227
-I'm just saying,
I hope it's worth it.

21:12.327 --> 21:14.329
-Yeah.

21:20.134 --> 21:21.796
Nice.

21:21.896 --> 21:24.758
-I dreamed about him last night,
lying alone.

21:24.858 --> 21:25.959
-Maybe he found the others.

21:26.060 --> 21:27.601
-If I'd known,
I would've gone back.

21:27.701 --> 21:30.043
-Which is why I did you
the favor of not telling you.

21:30.143 --> 21:32.165
-We could have at least tried!

21:32.265 --> 21:33.606
-I'm not arguing about this!

21:33.707 --> 21:36.049
-For all we know,
he was still alive.

21:36.149 --> 21:38.051
-There's nothing
we could've done!

21:38.151 --> 21:40.333
If we tried, we'd be dead.
-You don't know that!

21:40.433 --> 21:42.214
-I do know!

21:42.314 --> 21:45.217
Until we get some drinking
water, we can't fight.

21:45.317 --> 21:46.739
If you need to be a hero,
you do that.

21:46.839 --> 21:48.660
I'll move on.

21:48.760 --> 21:50.142
Are you with me?

21:50.242 --> 21:52.023
Yes or no?!

21:52.123 --> 21:53.625
-And cut!

21:53.725 --> 21:54.986
Let's go again.
-That's a cut.

21:55.086 --> 21:56.668
We're going again.

21:56.768 --> 21:58.629
-Scene works better with Zoe
getting confrontational.

21:58.730 --> 22:00.191
-Yeah. April's idea.

22:00.291 --> 22:01.372
You know, at the first
production meeting,

22:01.452 --> 22:03.194
Miles had the same note.

22:03.294 --> 22:06.557
-Miles Daly? Really?
-Mm-hmm.

22:06.657 --> 22:08.699
-Picture's up.

22:14.384 --> 22:16.866
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:24.553 --> 22:26.755
-I heard you wanted to see us.

22:30.118 --> 22:33.181
-What are "dailies"?

22:33.281 --> 22:36.264
-They're unedited film.

22:36.364 --> 22:37.665
-What's that?

22:37.765 --> 22:40.388
-Little pieces of the movie.
Why?

22:40.488 --> 22:42.610
Did you find a way
to get them in?

22:46.974 --> 22:48.715
-Why do you need them?

22:48.815 --> 22:52.118
-We watch to see how production
is getting on,

22:52.219 --> 22:53.720
see if there's anything
we missed or

22:53.820 --> 22:55.682
if a scene needs to be re-shot.

22:55.782 --> 22:58.724
-If the actors
don't have chemistry.

22:58.825 --> 23:00.846
-So...

23:00.947 --> 23:04.810
if part of it is not good,
you do it all over again?

23:04.910 --> 23:07.853
-Exactly.

23:07.953 --> 23:10.055
-That's interesting.

23:10.155 --> 23:11.897
-Should we discuss how
we're planning to --

23:11.997 --> 23:13.698
-There.

23:13.798 --> 23:16.741
-Ah, there goes your dailies.

23:16.841 --> 23:19.864
She's got the thumb drive
in her panocha.

23:19.964 --> 23:22.106
-Yeah, that's why
she's walking funny.

23:22.206 --> 23:24.908
-Conjugal visit with Animal,
she hands it to him,

23:25.009 --> 23:27.070
he swallows it.

23:27.171 --> 23:29.813
Then you get the drive
when he shits it out.

23:32.015 --> 23:33.837
-Isn't that clever.

23:33.937 --> 23:37.880
♪♪♪

23:37.980 --> 23:42.044
-[ Grunting ]

23:42.144 --> 23:47.529
♪♪♪

23:47.629 --> 23:49.771
[ Man whistles ]

23:49.871 --> 23:59.881
♪♪♪

24:01.042 --> 24:11.051
♪♪♪

24:12.052 --> 24:16.316
♪♪♪

24:16.416 --> 24:18.918
-And rolling.
And action!

24:19.018 --> 24:20.600
-...could've done!

24:20.700 --> 24:22.761
If we tried, we'd be dead.
-You don't know that!

24:22.862 --> 24:24.763
-I do know!

24:24.863 --> 24:27.526
-So, nothing happened with you
and banana girl?

24:27.626 --> 24:31.329
-Well, we had drinks together.
-But nothing sexual.

24:31.429 --> 24:32.811
-No.
-And your girlfriend

24:32.911 --> 24:34.172
had her killed?

24:34.272 --> 24:36.574
-Yeah, well, I can't
prove it, but...

24:36.674 --> 24:37.775
I'm pretty sure
that's what happened.

24:37.875 --> 24:40.177
-Intense. Perrier?

24:40.278 --> 24:42.780
-Yeah, thanks.

24:42.880 --> 24:47.184
-Horrible, but also romantic.

24:47.284 --> 24:48.986
-That his ex
had someone whacked?

24:49.086 --> 24:51.768
-I'm just saying, Amara
must really love you.

24:53.930 --> 24:55.792
-Well, I mean, it's hard to get
past the fact

24:55.892 --> 24:57.994
that
she killed someone, but, uh...

24:58.094 --> 25:00.556
-If I cheated on my wife,
she'd divorce me,

25:00.656 --> 25:03.599
then write a thank-you letter
to the woman I cheated with.

25:03.699 --> 25:08.503
Let me tell you, the banana girl
story, that's your next film.

25:11.706 --> 25:14.169
-Well, that's if people
will even work with me

25:14.269 --> 25:16.451
when I'm out of here.
[ Music chimes over PA ]

25:16.551 --> 25:18.653
-Five minutes.

25:18.753 --> 25:21.936
-Look, I don't know Hollywood,
but in finance,

25:22.036 --> 25:23.657
as long as you're
turning a profit,

25:23.757 --> 25:26.059
nobody cares if you did time.
[ Music chimes over PA ]

25:26.160 --> 25:30.343
-Five minutes.
-Let's finance his next film.

25:30.444 --> 25:32.626
-Done.

25:32.726 --> 25:34.187
-But I thought the FBI
got all your money.

25:34.287 --> 25:37.350
-Well, they did.
Right?

25:37.450 --> 25:40.553
-All of it.
[ Laughing ]

25:40.653 --> 25:44.336
-Let's just say, uh,
when we get out, call us.

25:46.899 --> 25:48.040
[ Door opens, closes ]

25:48.140 --> 25:51.363
-Oh.
That's nice of you guys.

25:51.463 --> 25:53.445
-We believe in you.

25:53.545 --> 25:55.687
We both know how
talented you are.

25:55.787 --> 25:58.409
Plus, that stuff with Amara?

25:58.509 --> 26:01.492
That's a great love story.

26:01.592 --> 26:05.215
[ Water running ]

26:05.315 --> 26:08.458
-Love story. [ Chuckles ]

26:08.558 --> 26:11.261
♪♪♪

26:11.361 --> 26:15.104
-It's ringing.
-[ Labored breathing ]

26:15.205 --> 26:17.907
-Voicemail.
-Where is she?

26:18.007 --> 26:20.870
-I am sure
that she's on her way.

26:20.970 --> 26:22.471
Uh, Yonni, yeah,
just wondering --

26:22.571 --> 26:23.632
-Yoni.
-What?

26:23.732 --> 26:24.994
-Yoni.

26:25.094 --> 26:26.475
Yoni, just wondering
where you are.

26:26.575 --> 26:28.517
The contractions are coming
every four minutes,

26:28.617 --> 26:30.719
so, you know,
the sooner the better.

26:30.819 --> 26:31.920
Okay, thank you.

26:32.020 --> 26:35.803
-Another... [ Groans ]

26:35.903 --> 26:37.445
-Are you okay?

26:37.545 --> 26:39.287
Huh?
Where's the timer?

26:39.387 --> 26:40.888
-Fuck the timer!
-Okay.

26:40.988 --> 26:42.449
I'm gonna write
down the minutes.

26:42.550 --> 26:44.451
-[ Grunting ]

26:44.551 --> 26:47.454
Okay.
[ Breathing deeply ]

26:47.554 --> 26:48.815
-Are you okay?

26:48.915 --> 26:50.457
-You have to stop
asking me that.

26:50.557 --> 26:51.938
-Oh, okay.

26:52.038 --> 26:55.902
All right.
Okay, it's a text from Yoni.

26:56.002 --> 26:57.423
Uh...

26:57.523 --> 27:00.866
Oh, she couldn't find the place.
-What?

27:00.966 --> 27:02.508
-She thought she was
in the wrong place.

27:02.608 --> 27:04.550
-What?
-Okay.

27:04.650 --> 27:06.031
No, I mean,
I'm sure that she's --

27:06.131 --> 27:07.913
I'm sure she's still here, okay?

27:08.013 --> 27:09.955
I'm just gonna go
find her, okay?

27:10.055 --> 27:12.077
-Okay.
-Are you okay?

27:12.177 --> 27:14.078
-Look!
-Okay! All right!

27:14.179 --> 27:15.440
Okay, I'll be right back!

27:15.540 --> 27:18.723
Yoni!
[ Ankle monitor beeps ]

27:18.823 --> 27:21.725
Yoni!

27:21.826 --> 27:23.487
Yoni!

27:23.587 --> 27:28.171
[ Ankle monitor beeping ]

27:28.271 --> 27:31.534
Yoni!

27:31.635 --> 27:36.299
Yoni! Yoni!

27:36.399 --> 27:37.580
-Yes.

27:37.680 --> 27:39.382
Yes, yes!
Fucking brilliant!

27:39.482 --> 27:41.303
Was that not
a brilliant bit of film?

27:41.404 --> 27:43.265
-I don't have any headphones.
I can't hear anything.

27:43.365 --> 27:44.947
-You saw the shot,
though, right?

27:45.047 --> 27:46.388
-Yeah, I mean, it looked good...

27:46.488 --> 27:47.589
-That is the best thing
that Cath Nardini

27:47.689 --> 27:49.391
has ever done, hands down.

27:49.491 --> 27:51.953
And Oumou -- oh, fucking
heartbreaking.

27:52.053 --> 27:53.395
What a performance.

27:53.495 --> 27:54.876
Hey, I-I got a couple of notes.

27:54.976 --> 27:55.997
Can you give me a few minutes?

27:56.097 --> 27:57.879
-I ain't here for that.

27:57.979 --> 27:59.800
From Swayze.

27:59.900 --> 28:02.543
He says Happy won't
bother you no more.

28:12.072 --> 28:14.574
-Have a little look in the bag,
see what it is, will you?

28:14.674 --> 28:16.916
-You look.
-No fuckin' chance.

28:24.603 --> 28:27.386
Oh, Jesus.

28:27.486 --> 28:29.928
[ Door buzzes ]

28:32.931 --> 28:35.013
Is that Happy's dick and balls?

28:37.895 --> 28:40.358
-I guess.

28:40.458 --> 28:43.120
-In pickle juice?

28:43.220 --> 28:46.843
What did they do
with the rest of him?

28:46.944 --> 28:49.025
We never asked for this.

28:51.308 --> 28:53.590
-I mean...

28:55.952 --> 28:58.614
All I said was, they should
keep him away from us.

28:58.714 --> 29:00.956
-Oh, no, no, no.
-I meant talk to him.

29:06.241 --> 29:08.543
-Seeing as it's your fault,
you get rid of it.

29:08.643 --> 29:11.206
Put it back in the bag,
get it off my bunk.

29:13.728 --> 29:17.191
-Actually, I'm gonna
stash it somewhere.

29:17.291 --> 29:20.154
-Y-You're gonna keep it?

29:20.254 --> 29:22.036
-I mean, if you need
someone to take you serious,

29:22.136 --> 29:23.597
you give 'em this.

29:23.697 --> 29:26.600
Right?
They'll know you're for real.

29:26.700 --> 29:28.001
And it's pickle juice.

29:28.101 --> 29:30.103
I mean, it's not gonna go --
-Get out.

29:32.185 --> 29:34.227
-Just sayin'...

29:37.710 --> 29:41.053
-Jesus Christ.

29:41.153 --> 29:43.455
-Focus on your breathing.
-[ Rhythmic breathing ]

29:43.555 --> 29:46.178
-That's it.

29:46.278 --> 29:48.060
You're doing so great.

29:48.160 --> 29:49.421
-You are, honey.
You're doing so good.

29:49.521 --> 29:51.062
-Want to lie on your side
for a while?

29:51.162 --> 29:52.584
-No.
[ Knock on door ]

29:52.684 --> 29:54.025
-Someone at the door.

29:54.125 --> 29:57.188
-Just ignore it.
-Police!

29:57.288 --> 29:59.310
-Did they say "police"?

29:59.410 --> 30:00.991
Louis...

30:01.092 --> 30:02.072
-Okay, I'll --
I'll be right back.

30:02.173 --> 30:05.636
-Breathe.
-[ Groaning ]

30:05.736 --> 30:07.477
-Hi.
Are you Louis Darnell?

30:07.577 --> 30:09.479
-Is this about
the ankle monitor?

30:09.579 --> 30:10.880
You Louis?
-Yeah, listen,

30:10.981 --> 30:12.722
I can't do this right now, guys.

30:12.822 --> 30:15.204
My wife is literally
giving birth --

30:15.305 --> 30:17.086
-Sir, are you Louis Darnell?

30:17.186 --> 30:18.287
-Yes! -Okay.

30:18.387 --> 30:19.348
We understand you're under house
arrest,

30:19.428 --> 30:21.090
and we just received an alert

30:21.190 --> 30:23.052
that you vacated the premises
during restricted hours.

30:23.152 --> 30:24.533
You are supposed to stay
in your house.

30:24.633 --> 30:27.255
-I'm having a fucking baby!
Okay?

30:27.356 --> 30:28.697
So if you guys want
to wait around

30:28.797 --> 30:30.098
until that's over with,
that's fine.

30:30.198 --> 30:32.700
But I can't do it
right now, okay?

30:32.801 --> 30:34.943
-All right, sir,
do not just walk away --

30:35.043 --> 30:36.304
-Goddammit...

30:36.404 --> 30:39.066
-Would you wait outside?!

30:39.166 --> 30:41.509
-Louis, come look.

30:41.609 --> 30:43.470
Louis, come stand next to me.

30:43.570 --> 30:46.954
[ Police radio chatter ]

30:47.054 --> 30:49.136
How beautiful is that?

30:52.859 --> 30:55.061
His head.

30:56.983 --> 30:59.325
[ Baby coos ]

30:59.425 --> 31:02.888
[ Children music plays ]

31:02.988 --> 31:05.691
[ Grunts ]

31:05.791 --> 31:07.092
Yeah.

31:07.192 --> 31:08.533
-Hey, if you make it
to the Safeway,

31:08.633 --> 31:10.895
there's a list in the kitchen.
-Okay.

31:10.996 --> 31:12.137
-What time do we have
to leave tonight?

31:12.237 --> 31:14.539
-Oh, the red carpet's at 6:00.
-Okay.

31:14.639 --> 31:17.742
I will be back at 5:00,
and I'll have Kenz here at 5:15.

31:17.842 --> 31:19.303
-Okay.
-My good baby.

31:19.403 --> 31:21.785
-Ooh. Guess what.

31:21.886 --> 31:24.788
We get to go grocery shopping.
Yeah.

31:24.888 --> 31:27.090
You get to ride in the cart.
Yeah.

31:33.416 --> 31:35.418
[ Door opens ]

31:36.099 --> 31:37.320
-Rick.

31:37.420 --> 31:40.282
[ Keys jingle ]

31:40.382 --> 31:41.764
-Yeah. Already?

31:41.864 --> 31:44.366
I -- I thought I had
a couple more hours.

31:44.466 --> 31:48.330
-It's time.

31:48.430 --> 31:51.292
-Okay. [ Chuckles ]

31:51.393 --> 31:54.335
-Everyone, Rick is out of here.

31:54.435 --> 31:56.417
[ Applause ]

31:56.517 --> 31:58.299
-Yeah.

31:58.399 --> 32:01.182
I got to be honest, guys...

32:01.282 --> 32:03.704
I don't want to go.
-Ah.

32:03.804 --> 32:06.587
You'll get home, friends and
family will throw you a party...

32:06.687 --> 32:09.109
-You'll forget all about us.

32:09.209 --> 32:11.311
-I don't think so.

32:11.411 --> 32:13.613
-Ah, come here, pal.
-All right.

32:16.656 --> 32:19.398
-Okay.
-Yeah. Thanks.

32:19.498 --> 32:21.921
-[ Grunts ]

32:22.021 --> 32:25.784
-Okay, guys.
Thanks, guys.

32:26.425 --> 32:28.527
[ Applause ]

32:28.627 --> 32:31.189
Thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you.

32:34.072 --> 32:38.416
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

32:38.516 --> 32:40.778
-Step in here.
-In here?

32:40.878 --> 32:43.120
-Yeah.

32:46.483 --> 32:48.885
-Hey. Thank you.

32:56.933 --> 32:59.195
-Nobody knows you're here
with me, right?

32:59.295 --> 33:02.157
-No, I'm here
on unrelated business.

33:02.258 --> 33:04.760
I remembered you were getting
out, thought I'd say hi.

33:04.860 --> 33:08.243
Take it your stay went well?

33:08.343 --> 33:11.246
-I've been as happy here
as I've ever been in my life.

33:11.346 --> 33:12.647
-That's...

33:12.747 --> 33:15.249
a better reaction
than I expected.

33:15.350 --> 33:17.892
-Any word on Amara?
-No, but do me a favor.

33:17.992 --> 33:21.575
If you notice anything unusual
when you're out, just...

33:21.675 --> 33:23.897
give us a call.

33:23.997 --> 33:26.420
-I just spent a year in prison
to throw people off.

33:26.520 --> 33:27.981
You're not telling me
I'm in danger.

33:28.081 --> 33:29.262
-Not necessarily.

33:29.362 --> 33:31.024
I mean, Amara's put out hits
on a few people,

33:31.124 --> 33:32.625
but there's no reason to think
that you're on her list.

33:32.725 --> 33:34.827
-Hits on who?

33:34.927 --> 33:38.871
-Just call us
if anything comes up.

33:38.971 --> 33:41.213
Better to err
on the side of caution.

33:48.340 --> 33:51.643
-So, you haven't seen them.
-I've heard they're good.

33:51.743 --> 33:54.405
-Just "good"?
Okay.

33:54.505 --> 33:56.667
-[ Chuckles ]

34:00.551 --> 34:02.933
"What could have been a campy
B-movie, or worse,

34:03.033 --> 34:05.415
an earnest,
derivative screed --"

34:05.515 --> 34:07.137
What's a screed?
-Screed --

34:07.237 --> 34:09.819
it's like a thorny plant,
lives in the desert --

34:09.920 --> 34:12.422
-"...derivative screed,
is instead an emotionally

34:12.522 --> 34:14.944
resonant exploration
of love and bravery

34:15.044 --> 34:16.506
in the modern age.

34:16.606 --> 34:19.909
Not to be missed."

34:20.009 --> 34:22.831
"Instead of making a desperate
play for the viewer's attention,

34:22.931 --> 34:26.074
'Wylderness' starts quietly,
yet we never look away,

34:26.174 --> 34:28.116
a credit to the
sure-handed filmmaking."

34:28.216 --> 34:30.919
-"Sure-handed"?
-Dad, they love it.

34:31.019 --> 34:32.360
-I mean, these are
early reviews.

34:32.460 --> 34:34.482
Let's see what the others say.

34:34.582 --> 34:36.524
-I'm proud of you.

34:36.624 --> 34:38.165
And so is Mom.

34:38.265 --> 34:41.488
As soon as it comes out,
we're all gonna go see it.

34:41.589 --> 34:43.690
-How is your mum?

34:43.791 --> 34:45.933
-Think she's gonna call you.

34:46.033 --> 34:49.656
But her and Philip are engaged.

34:49.756 --> 34:53.299
-Isn't that something.

34:53.399 --> 34:54.701
She in the back room?

34:54.801 --> 34:58.144
Why didn't she want to give me
the news herself?

34:58.244 --> 35:00.866
It's okay. It is.

35:00.966 --> 35:03.148
You like him, right?

35:03.248 --> 35:04.750
-He's nice to Mom.

35:04.850 --> 35:06.792
-How's he with you?

35:06.892 --> 35:09.274
-He's nice.

35:09.374 --> 35:10.555
Kind of boring...
[ Both chuckle ]

35:10.655 --> 35:12.357
But he's got a boat.

35:12.457 --> 35:14.879
-What kind of boat?
-I don't know boats.

35:14.979 --> 35:17.361
Medium-sized?

35:17.461 --> 35:19.363
Took us to Catalina.

35:19.463 --> 35:21.165
-I thought your mom
hated being at sea?

35:21.265 --> 35:23.287
-Yeah, she spent the whole trip
trying not to puke.

35:23.387 --> 35:25.088
-[ Laughs ]

35:25.188 --> 35:26.410
Oh, and she's gonna spend
a whole marriage

35:26.510 --> 35:29.172
feeling slightly seasick?

35:29.272 --> 35:31.354
-Well, I guess
she's okay with that.

35:34.077 --> 35:36.399
-I guess so.

35:38.481 --> 35:40.763
Is there only one?
Come on, there's one more.

35:44.046 --> 35:47.109
[ Cellphone rings ]

35:47.209 --> 35:50.031
-Hello?
-"An emotionally resonant film

35:50.131 --> 35:52.313
about love in the modern age.

35:52.413 --> 35:53.955
This is not to be missed."

35:54.055 --> 35:55.636
-I saw that.
-"We can't look away,

35:55.736 --> 35:56.998
not even for a moment.

35:57.098 --> 35:58.639
Our hearts will not allow it."

35:58.739 --> 36:00.521
-For someone with no Internet
access,

36:00.621 --> 36:02.563
you're very up
to date on reviews.

36:02.663 --> 36:05.405
-On the glowing reviews, April.
On the --

36:05.505 --> 36:08.008
Hey, when you were making
those films with Vin Diesel,

36:08.108 --> 36:09.409
were you getting
reviews like these?

36:09.509 --> 36:12.412
-Some critics
actually like explosions.

36:12.512 --> 36:15.174
But, uh, Miles, I, uh --

36:15.274 --> 36:16.976
I have to --
-What about theatrical release?

36:17.076 --> 36:18.818
Feels like,
with press like this,

36:18.918 --> 36:20.259
we should be
in more theaters, right?

36:20.359 --> 36:23.422
-Miles I have some
really shitty news.

36:23.522 --> 36:25.023
Like, I can barely say this.

36:25.123 --> 36:27.626
-What?
-Laurence filed with the PGA

36:27.726 --> 36:29.467
to have your name
taken off the film.

36:29.567 --> 36:32.590
-[ Chuckles ]

36:32.690 --> 36:34.232
What -- What do you mean?

36:34.332 --> 36:37.475
He can't take my name
off the film.

36:37.575 --> 36:38.796
It must be in the contract.

36:38.896 --> 36:41.599
-Contractually, he can do it.

36:41.699 --> 36:44.841
And he's on the board
of the PGA.

36:44.942 --> 36:47.084
Miles, I freaked out
when I found out.

36:47.184 --> 36:49.246
I called Laurence,
and I called the union.

36:49.346 --> 36:51.007
No one understands
how much input you've had on --

36:51.107 --> 37:01.297
♪♪♪

37:01.397 --> 37:11.406
♪♪♪

37:12.287 --> 37:22.296
♪♪♪

37:23.417 --> 37:33.426
♪♪♪

37:35.308 --> 37:44.656
♪♪♪

37:44.756 --> 37:46.618
[ Telephone rings ]

37:46.718 --> 37:49.160
-Laurence Budd's office.

37:54.445 --> 37:55.546
[ Telephone beeps ]

37:55.646 --> 37:57.828
Uh, it's Miles Daly.

37:57.928 --> 37:59.950
-Miles Daly?

38:00.050 --> 38:02.072
From, uh, prison?

38:02.172 --> 38:04.955
-Yeah, recording says
it's a collect call from Miles

38:05.055 --> 38:08.678
at the Porterville
Federal Penitentiary.

38:08.778 --> 38:11.841
-Amazing. Amazing.

38:11.941 --> 38:17.046
Okay.
Uh, I'll accept the charges.

38:17.146 --> 38:20.689
-Laurence.
Thanks for taking the call.

38:20.789 --> 38:22.571
-Thank you for reaching out.

38:22.671 --> 38:24.933
-I just wanted to congratulate
you on "Wylderness."

38:25.033 --> 38:27.696
From what I understand,
it's a very successful film.

38:27.796 --> 38:29.698
Another feather
in your well-feathered cap.

38:29.798 --> 38:32.660
-That's very kind.
-Of course.

38:32.760 --> 38:34.742
I've learned so much
from you already.

38:34.842 --> 38:37.184
Can't wait to put it
all into practice.

38:37.285 --> 38:38.706
-Well, I'm sorry
you weren't around

38:38.806 --> 38:42.549
for more of the filmmaking.
-Me too.

38:42.649 --> 38:45.672
-But down the road,
if you ever need anything,

38:45.772 --> 38:47.554
a recommendation,
an introduction...

38:47.654 --> 38:51.558
-Yes, I know you have friends
in very high places.

38:51.658 --> 38:54.320
Don't you golf
with the Attorney General?

38:54.420 --> 38:55.681
-Where did you hear that?

38:55.781 --> 38:57.363
-I've met some fascinating

38:57.463 --> 38:59.565
people myself
this last year, Laurence.

38:59.665 --> 39:02.888
Maybe someday we can
all get together.

39:02.988 --> 39:05.170
-We'll see.
-Yeah, I think there's gonna be

39:05.270 --> 39:07.732
a lot you're gonna
be able to do for me.

39:07.833 --> 39:09.374
-Is there.
-You know what I love the most

39:09.474 --> 39:11.736
about you, Laurence?

39:11.836 --> 39:13.698
You've got balls.

39:13.798 --> 39:15.700
-What?

39:15.800 --> 39:25.809
♪♪♪

39:27.651 --> 39:30.774
[ Dog barking in distance ]

39:38.340 --> 39:40.202
-Thank you.

39:40.302 --> 39:45.607
♪♪♪

39:45.707 --> 39:48.169
[ Keys jingle ]

39:48.270 --> 39:51.072
♪♪♪

40:09.489 --> 40:11.491
[ Button clicks ]

40:18.097 --> 40:19.598
[ Phone ringing ]

40:19.698 --> 40:21.600
-It's Kevin.
I'll get back to you.

40:21.700 --> 40:22.961
Thanks.
[ Phone beeps ]

40:23.061 --> 40:25.564
-Hey, it's, uh, dad.

40:25.664 --> 40:27.686
I'm home.

40:27.786 --> 40:29.647
I, uh...

40:29.748 --> 40:32.630
I don't know if you --
you got my messages.

40:35.353 --> 40:39.096
Martha said that
you might be in LA.

40:39.196 --> 40:42.559
But, uh, maybe --
maybe you're out of town.

40:44.962 --> 40:47.424
Anyway, uh...

40:47.524 --> 40:50.827
give me a call sometime.

40:50.927 --> 40:53.169
I don't have a lot scheduled.

40:57.533 --> 40:59.535
[ Telephone beeps ]

41:01.136 --> 41:03.078
[ Dog barking in distance ]

41:03.178 --> 41:08.403
♪♪♪

41:08.503 --> 41:12.607
♪♪♪

41:12.707 --> 41:15.690
[ Door creaks open ]

41:15.790 --> 41:18.532
[ Door closes ]

41:18.632 --> 41:19.853
Hey!

41:19.954 --> 41:21.055
-I got something
for you from Amara.

41:21.155 --> 41:22.056
-Oh, fuck.
No, no, no!

41:22.156 --> 41:23.457
No, no!
-Hold on.

41:23.557 --> 41:26.099
Calm down.

41:26.199 --> 41:28.702
She's waiting for you.
-What?

41:28.802 --> 41:31.644
-Ticket to Guatemala,
first-class.

41:37.930 --> 41:41.153
-Amara's in Guatemala?
-I guess.

41:41.253 --> 41:43.235
She said to give you this,
and she would have someone

41:43.335 --> 41:45.317
meet you at the airport.

41:45.417 --> 41:48.760
-It's one-way.

41:48.860 --> 41:51.382
You talk to her?
-Not often.

41:53.825 --> 41:56.967
-Is that hair real?
-No.

41:57.068 --> 41:58.889
-Looks real.

41:58.989 --> 42:00.971
-Have a good night.

42:01.071 --> 42:05.295
-Wait, wait. Wait.

42:05.395 --> 42:07.938
Want to have a drink?

42:08.038 --> 42:10.660
One thing I couldn't get
on the inside.

42:10.760 --> 42:12.922
I got vodka, got scotch.

42:15.004 --> 42:16.866
-Vodka.

42:16.966 --> 42:20.189
-Yeah. Yeah.

42:20.289 --> 42:22.291
Here.

42:23.892 --> 42:27.556
[ Indistinct conversations ]

42:27.656 --> 42:29.157
-Laurence, Laurence!
Laurence.

42:29.257 --> 42:30.919
The buzz for this film
is so good.

42:31.019 --> 42:33.761
Are you at all worried
about living up to the hype?

42:33.861 --> 42:36.484
-Well, it's a --
it's a great problem to have.

42:36.584 --> 42:38.806
I think people make up
their own minds.

42:38.906 --> 42:42.569
Oh! Here's our "Emile,"
the fantastic David Oumou.

42:42.669 --> 42:45.092
Look at him, fantastic.
Just stay right here.

42:45.192 --> 42:48.014
We were thinking,
let's make a genre film

42:48.114 --> 42:51.377
that is about character,
that goes deeper than usual.

42:51.477 --> 42:53.379
April. April Quinn --

42:53.479 --> 42:55.701
she's worked on this film
from its conception.

42:55.801 --> 42:57.343
April, let's take pictures, eh?

42:57.443 --> 43:00.586
-No, I'll leave you to it.
-Uh, thanks, everyone.

43:00.686 --> 43:03.629
Excuse me.

43:03.729 --> 43:05.791
-David! David.

43:05.891 --> 43:08.913
David, this is McG.

43:09.014 --> 43:11.956
-Brother, I am such a fan.
-Thank you so much.

43:12.056 --> 43:13.638
-David's doing a project
with Jennifer Lawrence.

43:13.738 --> 43:15.359
-Oh.
-Actually, we had a conflict.

43:15.459 --> 43:17.121
-No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no,
no. I'm gonna iron that out.

43:17.221 --> 43:19.603
McG here made
a whole bunch of those

43:19.703 --> 43:22.526
"Charlie's Angels" movies.
How awesome is that?

43:22.626 --> 43:24.808
He's working on -- is it four?
Number four?

43:24.908 --> 43:29.532
-Well, you ever do get busted --
God forbid --

43:29.632 --> 43:32.135
I recommend King Bush Prison.

43:32.235 --> 43:34.817
Amenities, great people.

43:34.917 --> 43:38.541
I can't say enough about it.
-Okay.

43:38.641 --> 43:40.943
-So, what have you been doing?

43:41.043 --> 43:43.865
-I was a bouncer in San Pedro.

43:43.966 --> 43:49.030
-Why didn't you go with Amara?
-Man, she barely made it out.

43:49.130 --> 43:52.353
And Guatemalan jungle,
that's not my thing.

43:52.453 --> 43:57.838
[ Jazz music plays ]

43:57.938 --> 43:59.680
You gonna use that ticket?

43:59.780 --> 44:01.602
-Well, I gotta level with you...

44:01.702 --> 44:04.444
It's a nice gesture, but, uh...

44:04.544 --> 44:08.088
Amara's had a lot
of other boyfriends, right?

44:08.188 --> 44:12.972
And those relationships
did not end very well.

44:13.072 --> 44:15.414
-But, she didn't marry them.

44:15.514 --> 44:18.437
You got way more of a connection
than those guys.

44:21.400 --> 44:23.642
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

44:26.364 --> 44:28.026
Thanks for the drink.

44:28.126 --> 44:30.268
-Hey.

44:30.368 --> 44:33.711
I got a frozen Shepard's Pie,
if you're hungry.

44:33.811 --> 44:35.873
Hmm?
About to heat it up.

44:35.973 --> 44:37.875
-No, thanks.

44:37.975 --> 44:41.518
You take care.
-Okay.

44:41.618 --> 44:44.441
[ Door opens, closes ]

44:44.541 --> 44:48.204
♪♪♪

44:48.304 --> 44:51.007
[ Car engine starts ]

44:51.107 --> 45:01.116
♪♪♪

45:03.158 --> 45:12.747
♪♪♪

45:12.847 --> 45:22.856
♪♪♪

45:24.057 --> 45:27.240
-And, of course,
I can't take all the credit.

45:27.340 --> 45:30.924
Um, we all know
the massive amount of people

45:31.024 --> 45:34.927
who lend their efforts
to projects of this magnitude,

45:35.027 --> 45:38.330
beginning with our amazing
director, Cath Nardini...

45:38.430 --> 45:41.733
[ Cheers and applause ]

45:41.834 --> 45:45.897
...our stellar cast...

45:45.997 --> 45:47.979
-This guy is the embodiment
of evil.

45:48.079 --> 45:51.262
-He is a douche.
-Stop humble bragging,

45:51.362 --> 45:52.904
you arrogant fuck.
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

45:53.004 --> 45:56.787
-...the story is very complex.
It's very deep.

45:56.887 --> 45:59.189
-Hey, buddy.
-I saw you called.

45:59.290 --> 46:01.552
You at the premiere?
-I am.

46:01.652 --> 46:05.355
Hold on.
-What's that in the background?

46:05.455 --> 46:07.998
-Uh, you know,
just people making speeches.

46:08.098 --> 46:09.959
-How lovely.

46:10.059 --> 46:13.282
-Can we just stop
and appreciate something?

46:13.382 --> 46:14.964
You weren't happy
when "The Admiral's Mistress"

46:15.064 --> 46:17.967
came out because maybe it wasn't
the greatest movie.

46:18.067 --> 46:19.968
But everybody --
I mean everybody --

46:20.069 --> 46:23.612
who has seen "Wylderness" says
that it is the shit!

46:23.712 --> 46:25.534
And, yeah, maybe your name's
not on it, and --

46:25.634 --> 46:29.137
and that's crazy,
but at least now you know

46:29.237 --> 46:32.560
that you can do this.
You got a gift, brother.

46:34.922 --> 46:36.704
-Is anyone there
talking about me?

46:36.804 --> 46:39.226
-No, they're too busy
listening to that bald,

46:39.326 --> 46:42.629
grandstanding asshole.

46:42.729 --> 46:44.991
-Let Laurence take his bow.

46:45.092 --> 46:47.514
He's earned it.

46:47.614 --> 46:49.836
-How's that?

46:49.936 --> 46:53.439
-Man makes his own movies,
he doesn't compromise,

46:53.539 --> 46:56.402
and he's fucking ruthless.

46:56.502 --> 46:58.404
I find that shit inspiring.

46:58.504 --> 47:01.006
I've been telling myself
what we do and what they do

47:01.106 --> 47:04.009
in Hollywood is basically
the same thing, only it's not.

47:04.109 --> 47:09.394
'Cause a man like Laurence,
he has no conscience, no honor.

47:11.516 --> 47:13.938
Maybe that's what's been
holding me back.

47:14.038 --> 47:15.539
When I get out,
anyone who gets in my way

47:15.639 --> 47:18.062
deserves what's fuckin'
coming to them.

47:18.162 --> 47:19.783
-Right.

47:19.883 --> 47:21.785
Okay, well, I can see that
you're in a pretty dark place,

47:21.885 --> 47:24.828
so, I'm not gonna blame you.
But you want to hear something?

47:24.928 --> 47:27.470
Here.
I want you to listen to this.

47:27.570 --> 47:32.635
[ Cheers and applause ]

47:32.735 --> 47:34.477
That's for you, man.

47:34.577 --> 47:36.839
For a movie that you made!

47:36.939 --> 47:39.401
[ Cheers and applause
continues ]

47:39.501 --> 47:41.823
-Yeah.

47:43.385 --> 47:47.709
[ Cheers and applause ]

47:52.713 --> 47:55.956
[ Indistinct conversations ]

48:00.921 --> 48:03.523
[ Electricity humming ]

48:13.292 --> 48:16.916
-It could use some furniture
and some paint.

48:17.016 --> 48:18.237
-That chair's cute.

48:18.337 --> 48:19.838
-Oh, thanks.
Yeah.

48:19.938 --> 48:22.241
Well, you have to start
somewhere.

48:22.341 --> 48:26.044
-Well, Gladys worked for Rick,
and that place was a dump.

48:26.144 --> 48:28.326
-Do you remember
that bathroom door --

48:28.426 --> 48:30.888
[ Banging on window ]
-Hey, Jim!

48:30.989 --> 48:33.050
Jim! Stay right there!

48:33.151 --> 48:35.152
I'll be right back.

48:40.197 --> 48:43.100
-I have no idea.

48:43.200 --> 48:45.142
So, how are you guys doing?

48:45.242 --> 48:48.064
-Oh, well, we're talking
real estate, too.

48:48.164 --> 48:51.027
Looking at houses.
It's all so pricey.

48:51.127 --> 48:54.230
-I know.
-So...

48:54.330 --> 48:56.112
when would I start?

48:56.212 --> 48:57.953
-As soon as you can.

48:58.053 --> 48:59.314
Right now, it's just me.

48:59.415 --> 49:01.917
I know this is a day job,
and you're a singer,

49:02.017 --> 49:05.560
and it's a new company,
so it could be a total disaster,

49:05.660 --> 49:07.162
but I would give you
more responsibility

49:07.262 --> 49:08.303
than you had with Rick,
and I pay better --

49:08.383 --> 49:10.124
-You don't have to
sell me on it.

49:10.224 --> 49:12.487
I'm excited.

49:12.587 --> 49:13.928
-Really?

49:14.028 --> 49:16.250
-Hey, Jim.

49:16.350 --> 49:17.932
It's Louis.

49:18.032 --> 49:21.535
And this is Wyatt.

49:21.635 --> 49:24.057
I'm David Oumou's manager.
We met at the premiere.

49:24.157 --> 49:25.739
-Right, right.

49:25.839 --> 49:29.142
-Now, I know that David is
under contract with you guys.

49:29.242 --> 49:30.163
-Oh, we're looking forward
to working with him.

49:30.243 --> 49:31.384
-Yeah, he can't do it.

49:31.484 --> 49:33.145
He got a film...

49:33.246 --> 49:34.747
with Jennifer Lawrence.

49:34.847 --> 49:38.470
There's no way
he can pass that up.

49:38.570 --> 49:40.152
-What was your name?
-Louis.

49:40.252 --> 49:42.194
-'Cause we went over it
with David's agents.

49:42.294 --> 49:44.476
This contract is fin--
-Here's the thing, Jim.

49:44.576 --> 49:48.279
I'm not like David's other reps.

49:48.379 --> 49:50.581
This will get ugly really quick.

49:53.864 --> 49:56.727
So just find someone else
for the role.

49:56.827 --> 49:58.289
There's not that many lines.

49:58.389 --> 50:00.891
Right? Right?

50:00.991 --> 50:03.493
He agrees.

50:03.593 --> 50:06.276
[ Baby coos ]
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

50:09.319 --> 50:11.361
-Excuse me.

50:14.443 --> 50:16.385
Will you be having
dinner tonight?

50:16.485 --> 50:18.187
-Yes, uh...

50:18.287 --> 50:20.989
I'll have a glass of Cabernet
and the lamb.

50:21.089 --> 50:22.991
-Sorry, lamb is
the northbound flight.

50:23.091 --> 50:26.194
We have filet mignon.
-Ah, even better.

50:26.294 --> 50:28.636
-Try the lamb on the way back.

50:28.736 --> 50:30.999
-I don't know when
I'll be coming back.

50:31.099 --> 50:34.001
-Oh.
Do you live in Guatemala?

50:34.101 --> 50:36.203
-No, I've never been.

50:36.303 --> 50:39.366
-But you're not coming back?

50:39.466 --> 50:41.588
-Well, I hope to come back.

50:44.431 --> 50:46.513
-I'll get your wine.

50:53.759 --> 51:03.228
♪♪♪

51:03.328 --> 51:12.436
♪♪♪

51:12.537 --> 51:14.799
-What?

51:14.899 --> 51:22.245
♪♪♪

51:22.346 --> 51:23.647
-This is Laurence Budd.

51:23.747 --> 51:27.290
Was my security system
armed last night?

51:27.390 --> 51:31.294
Because I was home, asleep, and
somebody broke into my bathroom!

51:31.394 --> 51:33.776
My bathroom.
That's right.

51:33.876 --> 51:36.458
Well, they moved things around
and they -- they...

51:36.559 --> 51:38.981
left something.

51:39.081 --> 51:40.302
Oh, I don't know.

51:40.402 --> 51:42.704
It's -- Uh, it's --
It's -- It's...

51:42.804 --> 51:45.987
Aah!
[ Glass shatters ]

51:46.087 --> 51:50.311
Aah! Aah!

51:50.411 --> 51:52.874
Aah!

